		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2485">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I devour your magazine every month, and see myself reflected in many of its stories, most recently &ldquo;Organicity.&rdquo; My husband&rsquo;s cancer gives me ready access to prescription drugs: Vicodin, Morphine, Valium, Xanax &mdash; you name it. I start the day with pot and am high by 6 <span class="smallcaps">A.M.</span> From then on, I take whatever substance will dull the pain and keep me functioning.</p>

<p>Life and death exist simultaneously here. I tell myself that miracles can happen &mdash; <em>are</em> happening &mdash; but this is easier to believe when I am high.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Name Withheld<br></p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

